definition.value: An L-isoleucine derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-isoleucine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-leucine derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-leucine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-lysyl ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-lysine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-methionine derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-methionine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-phenylalanine derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-phenylalanine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-proline derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-proline with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-serine derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-serine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-threonine derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-threonine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-tryptophan derivative that is the ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-tryptophan with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-tyrosyl ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-tyrosine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An L-valyl ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-valine with the 3'-hydroxy group of AMP.
An organic phosphoramidate obtained by formal condensation of the phosphate group of AMP with the amino group of L-morpholine.
A 5'-phospho-(3'->5')-dinucleotide composed from two AMP residues.
A N-glycosyl-1,2,4-triazine that is the 6-aza analogue of thymidine.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 37 carbons in total with 3 double bonds.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 8,12-diethyl-3-vinylbacteriochlorophyll d.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 37 carbons in total with 2 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 37 carbons in total with 5 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 39 carbons in total with 3 double bonds.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 41 carbons in total with 5 double bonds.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 12-ethyl-8-propyl-3-vinylbacteriochlorophyll d.
A chlorophyllide obtained by hydrolysis of the terpenoid ester moiety of 12-ethyl-8-isobutyl-3-vinylbacteriochlorophyll d.
A ketoaldonic acid phosphate that is 3-deoxy-D-glycero-beta-D-galacto-nonulosonic acid carrying a monophosohate substituent at position 9.
A lysophosphatidylcholine in which the remaining acyl group (position unspecified) contains 15 carbons and 2 double bonds.
A steroid compound with a structure based on a 18-carbon (estrane) skeleton.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 3-bromopyruvic acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A deaminoneuraminic acid in which the anomeric centre has beta-configuration.
A synthetic cholanoid that is a sulfonic acid analogue of chenodeoxycholic acid.
An organosulfonate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of 3alpha,7alpha-dihydroxy-5beta-cholane-24-sulfonic acid.
A CMP-sugar having 3-deoxy-D-glycero-beta-D-galacto-nonulosonic acid as the sugar component.

A member of the class of 1,3-thiazoles carrying 3,4,4-trifluorobut-3-ene-1-sulfonyl and chloro substituents at positions 2 and 5 respectively. A nematicide that is effective against a number of plant parasitic nematodes in a range of agricultural and horticultural crops.

A benzamide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-[benzoyl(methyl)amino]-2-fluorobenzoic acid with the amino group of 2-bromo-4-(1,1,1,2,3,3,3-heptafluoropropan-2-yl)-6-(trifluoromethyl)aniline. An insecticide that exhibits high larvicidal activity against Spodoptera litura and is effective against pests with resistance to cyclodienes and fipronil

A pyridopyrimidine that is 9-methyl-2,4-dioxo-2H-pyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidine substituted at positions 1 and 3 by (2-chloro-1,3-thiazol-5-yl)methyl and 3,5-dichlorophenyl groups respectively. A mesoionic insecticide used for control of rice hoppers.
An organonitrogen heterocyclic compound that is 1H,5H-[1,4]dithiino[2,3-c:5,6-c']dipyrrole-1,3,5,7(2H,6H)-tetrone substituted at positions 2 and 6 by methyl groups.
An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of pyrazine-2-carboxylic acid with the amino function of 3',4'-difluoro[1,1'-biphenyl]-2-amine.
A CMP-sugar having 8-amino-3,8-dideoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid as the sugar component.
A disaccharide phosphate that is sucrose carrying a single monophosphate substituent at position 6 on the glucose ring.
Any bacterial metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Mycoplasma genitalium.
A carboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of a dicarboxylic acid monoester.
A dipeptide that is L-methionyl-L-methionine (Met-Met) in which the nitrogen of the N-terminal amino group has been converted into the corresponding formamide.
A tertiary alcohol that is isopropanol in which the hydrogen attached to the carbon bearing the hydroxy group has been replaced by a phenyl group.
A dipeptide formed from two L-cysteine residues.

An echinocandin initially isolated as a very minor bioactive fermentation product of Glarea lozoyensis (originally known as Zalerion arboricola). Subsequent random mutagenesis work and optimisation of the fermentation medium permitted the industrial production of pneumocandin B0, which is used as the starting point for the synthesis of the antifungal drug caspofungin.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue derived from O-(beta-L-arabinofuranosyl)-trans-4-hydroxy-L-proline.
Any compound that inhibits the biosynthesis of teichoic acid.

A member of the class of oxazolidinones that is oxazolidin-2-one substituted at positions 3, 4 and 5 by (naphthalen-1-yl)acetyl, methyl and 3,5-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups respectively. An inhibitor of teichoic acid biosynthesis.

A member of the class of benzimidazoles that is the amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(2-cyclohexylbenzimidazol-1-yl)propanoic acid with the amino group of (1R,2R,4R)-1,7,7-trimethylbicyclo[2.2.1]heptan-2-amine. An inhibitor of teichoic acid biosynthesis.

A member of the class of oxazolidinones that is oxazolidin-2-one substituted at positions 3, 4 and 5 by 3-(isoquinolin-4-yl)propanoyl, methyl and 3,5-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups respectively. An inhibitor of teichoic acid biosynthesis.

A member of the class of oxazolidinones that is oxazolidin-2-one substituted at positions 3, 4 and 5 by 3-(isoquinolin-4-ylmethyl)carbamoyl, methyl and 3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl groups respectively. An inhibitor of teichoic acid biosynthesis.
A beta-D-glucoside derived from formal condensation of the hydroxy group of 5-(hydroxymethyl)cytosine with the anomeric hydroxy group of D-glucopyranose.
